1) Introduction

1.1) The game of HEX
HEX is a two player board game invented in 1942. It was rediscovered in the late 1940s and first marketed in 1952. It has simple rules, but a high number of possible moves. The board with n*n hexagons can have any possible size. However, it is usually played on boards with n of 11, 13 or 19. Figure PICTURE presents an example board. In the beginning of the game, the board is empty. Each player is assigned two parallel edges of the board. Then, the players alternate, placing objects of their color on an empty hexagon. Their goal is to place their objects in a chain, that connects their assigned edges. Usually, the player that places the first object would have an advantage. For this reason, the swap rule can be used. It defines, that after one player places the first object, the other player is allowed to choose which color they pick.
(https://www.hexwiki.net/index.php)

